2.00	Bhiksuni	Bhikkhuni	A bhikkhuni or bhikṣuṇī (Sanskrit) is a fully ordained female Buddhist monastic. Male monastics are called bhikkhus. Both bhikkhunis and bhikkhus live by the vinaya. Bhikkhuni lineages enjoy a broad basis in Mahayana countries like Korea, Vietnam, China, and Taiwan.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/eb/Taiwanese_Buddhist_Nun_Black_Robes.jpeg/170px-Taiwanese_Buddhist_Nun_Black_Robes.jpeg
